706943f-b.title: Brooklyn: Surf Avenue - 5th Street (West)
706943f-b.text:
(1)
Surf Ave., north side, west of West 5th Street, showing in the fore-
ground, the car barns of the Manhattan Transit R.R. Co., and beyond it
the Brooklyn Edison Co's branch building. On the site of the car ter-
minal, once stood the Vanderveer Concourse Hotel, which was opened on
December 10, 1878. It was demoished in 1902.
December 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
(2)
The same, looking eastward.
January 1924.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
